Sent: 21 August 2015 5:15 PM
To: CL-DISPATCH
Cc: SEC [ETSI Secretariat Distribution List]; STFs [All active STF experts]
Subject: ETSI CL15_3221: Invitation to the 1st 6lo PlugtestsTM event, 6-8 N=
ovember 2015, in Yokohama, Japan

The complete file (and annexes if any) of this Collective Letter can be dow=
nloaded at the following location: http://docbox.etsi.org/C_Letter/CL2015/C=
L15_3221_Invitation_6lo_Plugtests.doc

To:              ETSI MEMBERS, OBSERVERS AND COUNSELLORS
Subject:     Invitation to the 1st 6lo PlugtestsTM event, 6-8 November 2015=
, in Yokohama, Japan

Dear Madam,
Dear Sir,

ETSI's Centre for Testing and Interoperability (CTI) is organizing the 1st =
6lo (IPv6 over Networks of Resource-constrained Nodes) Plugtests(tm) event.=
 This event will be held from 6 to 8 November 2015 in Yokohama, Japan, with=
 the support of the Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF) 6lo Working Grou=
p, co-located with the 94th IETF meeting (1 to 6 November 2015).

This Plugtests(tm) event will focus on assessing the interoperability of di=
fferent implementations based on the 6LoWPAN specifications RFC4944, RFC628=
2 and RFC6775 adapted to:
-       Constrained wired networks (draft-ietf-6lo-6lobac-02)
-       DECT Ultra Low Energy air interface (draft-ietf-6lo-dect-ule-02)
-       Bluetooth low energy air interface* (draft-ietf-6lo-btle-17)
-       Near Field Communication* (NFC) radio interface* (draft-ietf-6lo-nf=
c-01)

(* if number of implementations permits)

The testing campaign will be based on the test cases developed by ETSI in c=
ollaboration with IETF 6lo WG members and will focus on the interoperabilit=
y of these different technologies.

It will give a unique opportunity to participating 6lo vendors to test thei=
r product against different implementations.

Vendors participating in this event will also benefit from a great deal of =
communication and marketing.

The event is free of charge and is open to both ETSI members and non-member=
s.

All information related to this event along with registration details may b=
e found at the following address: http://www.etsi.org/news-events/events/10=
03-6lo-plugtests.

You can also contact us via email: Plugtests@etsi.org<mailto:Plugtests@etsi=
.org>.

Yours faithfully,


Luis Jorge Romero Saro
Director-General


